Citation.sTitle: Volumetric behaviour of binary liquid systems composed of toluene, isooctane, and methyl tert-butyl ether at temperatures from (298.15 to 328.15) K
Citation.sAbstract: The densities and speeds of sound of (toluene + isooctane), (MTBE + toluene), and (MTBE + isooctane)  were measured at four temperatures from (298.15 to 328.15) K, and the respective values of excess volumes  VE  m and adiabatic compressibility jS were calculated. The VE  m and jS values were fitted to the  fourth-order Redlich Kister equation. The VE  m values for (MTBE + toluene) are negative and decreasing  with increasing temperature. The other systems show positive VE  m with comparatively small temperature  dependence.
